Our Story

Honoring Culture, One Plate at a Time

Kimo & Melia's Hawaiian Grindz was born from a deep love of Hawaiian culture and the flavors that connect us to our kupuna (elders). Every dish we prepare carries the spirit of generations pastthe same recipes that filled our family tables and warmed our hearts.

As Native Hawaiians, we believe food is more than nourishmentit's a way of preserving our heritage and sharing aloha with our community. From the rich, smoky kalua pig cooked in the traditional imu to the comforting embrace of fresh poi, each plate tells a story of the islands.

Taste the Tradition

Each dish is crafted with love, using time-honored recipes passed down through generations

Signature

Kalua Pig

Pua'a Kalua

Slow-roasted pork prepared in the traditional Hawaiian style, tender and smoky with rich, savory flavors.

Traditional

Lau Lau

Wrapped in Ti Leaves

Pork and butterfish wrapped in taro and ti leaves, steamed to perfection.

Fresh Poi

Poi Hou

Hand-pounded taro, the sacred staple of Hawaiian cuisine. Creamy and deeply nourishing.

Lomi Salmon

Lomi Lomi Salmon

Fresh salmon massaged with tomatoes, onions, and green onions. Refreshing and bright.

Chicken Long Rice

Moa me ke Long Rice

Clear noodles in a ginger-infused broth with tender chicken. Soul-warming comfort.

Squid Luau

He'e Luau

Tender squid slow-cooked with taro leaves in rich coconut milk.
